Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.40,0:00:07.83,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Things were busy that summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.82,0:00:13.16,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The frequent disasters of the \Npast year probably played a role,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.95,0:00:16.31,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,but cursed spirits were \Nspringing up like maggots.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.41,0:00:47.78,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Exorcise, absorb.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:49.34,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.08,0:00:55.06,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Exorcise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.63,0:00:56.60,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Absorb.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.86,0:00:59.22,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,No one else understands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.92,0:01:01.52,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,what cursed spirits taste like.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.49,0:01:07.76,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,It's like swallowing a dirty rag that's \Nbeen used to clean up shit and vomit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.63,0:01:09.60,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Exorcise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.40,0:01:11.57,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Absorb.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.83,0:01:15.95,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,"What I witnessed isn't uncommon."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.95,0:01:17.89,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,"I understood the ugliness of the masses,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.64,0:01:24.30,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,and still chose to be a \Njujutsu sorcerer who saves others."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.36,0:01:30.04,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I've been telling \Nmyself ever since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.97,0:01:32.31,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.81,0:01:39.12,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, this used to be \Nthe home of the president
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.12,0:01:42.72,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,of a company managing a local \Nchain of barbecue restaurants.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.51,0:01:46.22,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,However, in July of last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.22,0:01:51.88,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,the mad cow disease breakout dealt \Na fatal blow to his restaurants,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:55.40,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,so he committed suicide with his family \Nafter they were buried under vast debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.40,0:01:59.36,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,From then on, local rumors claimed \Nthe president's home was haunted,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.63,0:02:02.37,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,so local school kids, college students \Nfrom outside the prefecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.79,0:02:05.96,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,job-hoppers, and others would visit \Nit as part of a test of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.96,0:02:07.83,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,and subsequently go missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.58,0:02:11.46,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Those rumors brought about more rumors,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:13.55,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,and the damage just continued to spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:18.88,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors do tend to spread rather \Nquickly around haunted spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:25.38,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They can spread at an unbelievable \Npace nowadays, thanks to the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.38,0:02:30.15,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This all just means even more \Nwork for us jujutsu sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.78,0:02:35.91,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,In addition to that, three grade school kids \Nwent missing on their way home from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.91,0:02:39.40,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,There's also a high chance \Nthe families, police, colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.40,0:02:43.16,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,and friends who trace the paths \Nof those who disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.16,0:02:45.52,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,will reach the mansion and \Nbecome victims themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:49.41,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,We have to sever the root of \Nthis issue as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:54.99,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,HQ sent us to investigate because \Nthey reached the same conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.75,0:02:57.75,sign_4502_41_Warning__Enterin,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)}Warning!\N{\fs20\c&H393542&\3c&H727051&}Entering These Premises Is Forbidden!\NMany Have Gone Missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.71,0:02:58.37,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They're even paying my fees, \Nwhich aren't cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:01.39,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Did you overcharge them again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.71,0:03:03.86,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You make it sound so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.86,0:03:06.16,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Call it negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.82,0:03:08.04,Main,Assistant Supervisor,0000,0000,0000,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:10.84,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.93,0:03:16.23,Show_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&H86C8C7&}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.23,0:03:18.60,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Emerge from darkness, blacker than darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:19.79,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Purify that—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.56,0:03:22.32,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for a veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:23.24,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.24,0:03:26.70,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't sense the presence of any Curses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.70,0:03:30.53,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The cause is almost certainly \Ninside the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:35.28,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You can cast the veil later if we \Nend up attacking it from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.79,0:03:37.00,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(175,0)\fnComic Sans MS\fs12\fsp2\c&H302510&\3c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\bord1\3a&H60&\pos(242.667,200)}...True.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.12,0:03:39.21,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.42,0:03:42.40,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like something's blocking the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.17,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.55,0:03:52.71,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Mei-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.72,0:03:54.80,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.56,0:03:57.35,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And it's all around us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.19,0:04:05.11,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:07.95,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need that, but you do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.80,0:04:11.27,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.91,0:04:14.45,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.17,0:04:27.96,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I-Incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.32,0:04:32.71,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it still has electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.95,0:04:37.26,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's have a \Nlook inside the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:39.07,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take this floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.07,0:04:40.74,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,you take the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.74,0:04:43.27,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? All by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.27,0:04:44.97,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.97,0:04:48.60,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, i-it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:50.35,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Off you go, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:54.80,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.38,0:05:39.04,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:30.56,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You could be the next big Scream Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.57,0:06:34.64,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:37.04,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't startle me like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:40.14,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You got startled all on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:43.81,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done exploring the first floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:48.52,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:50.53,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:54.32,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I was walking down \Nthe first floor hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:06:56.72,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,What? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.19,0:07:02.44,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I know I entered a room \Nat the end of the hallway...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:05.49,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A box of candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:07.63,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A bag of potato chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.14,0:07:08.67,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.08,0:07:10.51,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.84,0:07:12.17,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A sweatshirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.57,0:07:15.98,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I've already seen this three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.70,0:07:21.96,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And see these marks? I made \Nthem on my way through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.36,0:07:28.20,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that we're already \Nin the belly of the beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:30.43,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.86,0:07:37.56,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:43.66,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,How long {\i1}is{\i0} this hallway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.92,0:07:46.82,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We've been moving for thirty minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:49.08,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,so about four kilometers so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.98,0:07:53.04,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,It's not an innate domain, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.60,0:07:54.82,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.10,0:07:58.18,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Those are manifestations \Nof the spirit's mindscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:00.12,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.39,0:08:01.88,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,This is a barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:03.47,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.70,0:08:07.11,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, the victims \Nwere trapped inside this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:09.21,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and then killed by the cursed spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.96,0:08:14.56,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Though, considering the \Nuse of this technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.56,0:08:17.15,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,the cursed spirit itself should be weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.96,0:08:21.06,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So if we can just escape this barrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.87,0:08:25.74,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Now, quiz time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.74,0:08:29.11,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,How would you break this, Utahime?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.60,0:08:35.88,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,This hallway is repeating itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.88,0:08:37.72,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,At first...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:42.77,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.36,0:08:45.08,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you could touch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:47.94,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,...it was shaped like a donut.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:52.04,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,But we passed by four of \Nthe marks you made, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.44,0:08:55.69,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,When I calculated how many \Npaces apart they were, I got...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:57.30,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,122,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:08:58.44,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,203,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.44,0:08:59.76,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,157,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:00.69,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,and 270 paces.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.29,0:09:05.04,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,So the spacing between marks was random.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:06.66,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:11.21,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,The interval between \Nrepetitions isn't standardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.76,0:09:14.72,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:17.80,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,this barrier is patching spaces together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.41,0:09:23.38,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,So if we both run down the hallway \Nat top speed, then at some point...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.49,0:09:28.48,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,It'll break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.45,0:09:32.39,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Close. Ninety points.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.39,0:09:33.40,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,D'oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.91,0:09:35.64,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,What's the remaining ten?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:41.53,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,When we run, we do so in opposite \Ndirections at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.53,0:09:43.07,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.07,0:09:45.13,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,So my patching theory was correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.13,0:09:47.90,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,and if we quickly advance \Nin different directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.90,0:09:51.19,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,that makes it harder for the cursed \Nspirit to hold the barrier together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:54.19,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,And once we have that opening, \Nwe might be able to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:55.34,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,One hundred points.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:56.84,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Then, with that settled...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.59,0:10:01.68,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,If this works, I'll be expecting a promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:04.55,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,How much do you have in savings?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.55,0:10:05.37,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:08.72,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind. I'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:09.78,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:14.14,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Okay... Ready, set...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:16.16,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.40,0:10:22.69,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:24.95,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.28,0:10:45.34,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to save you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:49.06,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Utahime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.56,0:11:03.32,Show_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1000)\pos(320,10)}JUJUTSU KAISEN\N{\fs16\bord0\fscy100}Hidden Inventory/Premature Death
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.96,0:12:21.30,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(530,173)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&}m 0 0 l 140 0 l 140 200 l 0 200
Dialogue: 1,0:12:18.96,0:12:21.30,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(530,173)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs14\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Jujutsu High\NSecond-Year\N{\fs30}Satoru\NGojo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.86,0:12:21.30,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:23.24,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:26.51,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(75,95)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&}m 0 0 l 100 0 l 100 140 l 0 140
Dialogue: 1,0:12:21.30,0:12:26.51,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(75,95)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs12\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Second-grade\NSorcerer\N{\fs24}Utahime\NIori
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:24.47,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,And be more polite!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:26.51,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If I was crying, would you console me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:29.26,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(558,120)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&}m 0 0 l 140 0 l 140 200 l 0 200
Dialogue: 1,0:12:26.51,0:12:29.26,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(558,120)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}First-grade\NSorcerer\N{\fs30}Mei Mei
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.11,0:12:29.26,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'd certainly appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.71,0:12:31.87,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, you wouldn't cry, Mei-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.03,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,You're strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.19,0:12:35.35,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.39,0:12:39.02,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Gojo! You listen here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:40.44,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your hel—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.27,0:12:46.33,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Don't swallow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:48.35,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I'll absorb it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.19,0:12:51.95,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Satoru, it's not nice to pick on the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.95,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(548.5,157)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&}m 0 0 l 136 0 l 136 200 l 0 200
Dialogue: 1,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.95,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(548.5,157)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs14\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Jujutsu High\NSecond-Year\N{\fs30}Suguru\NGeto
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:55.19,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of idiot picks on the strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.95,0:12:59.56,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one fanning the flames \Nlike it comes naturally, Geto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.22,0:13:03.03,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Utahime-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:05.34,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:06.59,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:10.72,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(480,187)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&\bord0}m 0 0 l 136 0 l 136 200 l 0 200
Dialogue: 1,0:13:05.34,0:13:10.72,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(480,187)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs14\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Jujutsu High\NSecond-Year\N{\fs30}Shoko\NIeiri
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.59,0:13:08.71,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:10.72,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,We hadn't heard from you for two whole days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:13.72,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.05,0:13:18.65,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko! Don't let yourself \Nturn out like those two!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:21.64,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,I won't turn into trash like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.23,0:13:26.53,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\p1\c&HF8F9F6&\bord0\shad0\an5\pos(78,186)\clip(m 48 119 l 102 116 104 253 54 255)}m 0 0 l 50 0 l 50 140 l 0 140
Dialogue: 1,0:13:20.23,0:13:26.53,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\fnArial\pos(78,184)\an5\fs20\c&H323331&\shad0\bord0}Said\NTrash
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.64,0:13:24.71,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,The path Utahime walked is falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:26.21,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:29.23,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, two days?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.02,0:13:34.32,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, was the cursed spirit's barrier \None of those that messes with time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.32,0:13:36.54,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,They're rare, but they \Ndo happen now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:39.43,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was odd, \Nsince Mei-san was with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.91,0:13:41.51,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.68,0:13:43.64,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:48.05,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,No. Just realized that means \Nit was actually two days' labor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:52.73,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and that means extra fees paid out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.73,0:13:55.14,Main,Utahime,0000,0000,0000,,She's planning to overcharge again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.14,0:13:58.27,Main,Mei Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, what about the veil, you three?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:05.65,Sign_Basic,screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HBBAD98&\shad0\c&HE1E0D0&\fs16\an7\fax-.3\bord1\fsp2\pos(414,75.333)}White\N\h\hNews
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:05.65,Sign_Basic,screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HB05D47&\shad0\c&HE1E0D0&\fs15\pos(453,250)\an3}Degradation of gas pipes causes explosion
Dialogue: 1,0:14:02.27,0:14:06.08,Italics,Announcer,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Next, the explosion that occurred \Nyesterday in Hamamatsu, Shizuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.04,0:14:09.24,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,One of you three said they \Nwould cast the veil themselves
Dialogue: 1,0:14:06.08,0:14:08.58,Italics,Announcer,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The explosion was caused \Nby degradation of gas pipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:10.15,Italics,Announcer,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Our reporter on the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.24,0:14:12.57,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,and left your assistant \Nsupervisor behind, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:15.11,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,And then you forgot the veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.58,0:14:15.12,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(531.5,166)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HF9F9F9&}m 0 0 l 126 0 l 126 184 l 0 184
Dialogue: 1,0:14:12.58,0:14:15.12,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(531.5,166)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}First-grade\NSorcerer\N{\fs29}Masamichi\NYaga
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.11,0:14:16.46,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Come forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.82,0:14:18.96,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:20.82,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we stop this hunt for the culprit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.82,0:14:22.00,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,So it was you, Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.04,0:14:23.80,Sign_Basic,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\fs40\bord0\shad0\c&H000000&}Discipline
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:29.04,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Is a veil that necessary in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.68,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like it matters if \Nnormies see or not, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:35.43,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,They can't see cursed spirits \Nor cursed techniques, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:40.11,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it's not good for them to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.11,0:14:42.22,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The strongest deterrent \Nagainst the outbreak
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:45.41,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,of a cursed spirit is the \Nmental calm of the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.92,0:14:49.21,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly why we have to conceal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.21,0:14:51.90,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,the threats they can't even \Nsee as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.26,0:14:53.26,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:55.16,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.24,0:15:05.63,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Looking out for the weak \Nis so exhausting, honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.27,0:15:07.89,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Survival of the weakest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.89,0:15:10.46,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,That's how a society should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.75,0:15:13.56,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The weak help each other and \Ndiscourage any who are too strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:15.13,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:18.71,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Jujutsu exists to protect \Nnon-jujutsu sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:21.51,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your moral argument?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.87,0:15:24.73,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I hate moral arguments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.26,0:15:26.10,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.77,0:15:29.82,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Assigning reasons and \Nresponsibility to strength
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.82,0:15:32.53,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,is what those who are weak do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.41,0:15:46.27,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Quit making yourself feel \Nbetter by spouting bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:48.39,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Blegh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.39,0:15:50.20,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,Run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.54,0:15:53.47,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Want to take this outside, Satoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:55.51,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,You feeling lonely?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.50,0:15:56.88,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Go by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:01.61,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going \Nto keep fooling around?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.96,0:16:03.27,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Shoko go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.47,0:16:04.61,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.61,0:16:05.77,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Bathroom, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.65,0:16:07.77,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.77,0:16:10.60,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,This mission is being assigned to you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.71,0:16:13.53,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,What are those faces for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.96,0:16:15.11,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.84,0:16:18.49,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I think it's too much for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.91,0:16:20.94,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,but Tengen-sama asked for you specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.92,0:16:24.79,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Your mission has two goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:26.69,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Plasma Vessel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.02,0:16:29.14,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,is the one compatible with Tengen-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.14,0:16:33.26,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,You are to escort that girl and erase her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.63,0:16:36.27,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Escort a brat and erase her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.90,0:16:38.18,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:39.74,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Have you finally gone senile?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.94,0:16:41.52,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,It is spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.52,0:16:44.27,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably got his head full \Nwith being the next principal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:46.04,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Jokes aside, though—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:49.07,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'll be the one to decide \Nif I let that off as a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.53,0:16:50.42,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Is this about renewing \NTengen-sama's technique?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:52.94,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.26,0:16:57.53,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:01.25,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Tengen-sama possesses the \Ncursed technique of Immortality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.25,0:17:02.77,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,but it is not Eternal Youth.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:02.77,0:17:05.48,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be an issue \Nif all he did was get older,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.48,0:17:07.83,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,but after his body ages to a certain point,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:10.58,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,the cursed technique \Nbegins rewriting his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:13.48,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:17.01,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,He'll cease to be human and become \Na higher form of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.23,0:17:18.92,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.92,0:17:20.70,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:22.33,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,According to Tengen-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:26.37,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,those who reach that state \Nof being have no will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.67,0:17:29.77,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,It means Tengen-sama would \Ncease to be Tengen-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:31.52,Sign_Basic,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs16\fnTimes New Roman\c&H2A362B&\bord2\shad0\3c&H6C7A68&}Tokyo Jujutsu High School
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:31.52,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,All the jujutsu schools,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:33.97,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,the barriers that form the \Nfoundation of jujutsu society,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:36.34,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,the many barrier techniques \Nof the assistant supervisors...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.34,0:17:40.72,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,They're all being strengthened by Tengen-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:43.29,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Without the aid of his power,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:46.31,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,we could hardly maintain security \Nor clean up after missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:48.12,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,In the worst-case scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.12,0:17:51.63,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Tengen-sama could even become \Na threat to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.63,0:17:54.95,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, every 500 years, \Nhe finds the Star Plasma Vessel—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:17:58.35,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,someone who is compatible with him—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.35,0:18:00.51,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,and assimilates them, \Noverwriting the information of their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.91,0:18:02.75,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,By renewing his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.75,0:18:05.27,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,he resets his cursed \Ntechnique back to the start
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:07.03,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,and avoids Evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.03,0:18:08.44,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.44,0:18:10.99,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,It would be fine if he turned \Ninto MetalGreymon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.99,0:18:13.48,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,but we can't have him \Nbecoming SkullGreymon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.48,0:18:16.27,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,So we have him start over from Koromon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:19.75,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,What? Yeah, sure, that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.75,0:18:24.06,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Plasma Vessel's \Nlocation has been leaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.06,0:18:28.34,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, there are two major \Ngroups after the young girl's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.83,0:18:30.99,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,One is the Curse User Group Q,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.35,0:18:35.48,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,which seeks to upend jujutsu society \Nwith Tengen-sama's rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.56,0:18:40.02,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,The other is the Star Religious \NGroup, also known as the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.02,0:18:42.86,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,"Time Vessel Association,"\Nwhich worships Tengen-sama as a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:48.13,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Tengen-sama will assimilate the \NStar Plasma Vessel two days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.13,0:18:53.00,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,You are to protect the girl until then and \Nensure that she reaches Tengen-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:56.99,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,If you fail, the effects will ripple \Nthroughout even normal society!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:18:58.57,Main,Yaga,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:00.82,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.82,0:19:03.71,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I get why Curse User Group Q \Nwould be after her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.71,0:19:07.00,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,but why would this Star Religious \NGroup want to kill a brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.62,0:19:10.87,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Their object of worship is \Nthe pure form of Tengen-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.23,0:19:12.68,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Allowing the Star Plasma Vessel—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.68,0:19:16.43,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,in their minds, an impurity—\Nto blend into him is unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:20.07,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Religious Group is an \Norganization of non-sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:22.21,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we need to pay them any mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.43,0:19:24.88,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,The ones to be wary of are Q.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.17,0:19:27.05,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.05,0:19:28.89,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,We're the strongest, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:32.00,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Tengen-sama asked \Nfor us specifically, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.42,0:19:35.35,Italics,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.91,0:19:38.38,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Satoru...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.38,0:19:40.67,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I've been wanting to say this for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.67,0:19:43.20,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,but you should stop being \Nso full of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.51,0:19:45.03,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:48.79,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when you're \Naddressing your superiors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:51.39,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,We might end up meeting \NTengen-sama, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.39,0:19:55.04,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,You should be more polite and humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.04,0:19:57.27,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,You'd scare your juniors less, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.27,0:19:58.00,Italics,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Hah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.24,0:19:59.59,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:01.74,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.74,0:20:02.96,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:04.51,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring it up again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.15,0:20:10.13,Main,Kuroi,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.56,0:20:11.51,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.31,0:20:19.52,Italics,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,You alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.92,0:20:21.07,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,I am, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.02,0:20:25.03,Italics,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,You think we'll be blamed \Nif the brat died from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.93,0:20:26.32,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(135,231)\b1\bord3\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HE5E7E7&}Ah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.16,0:20:37.88,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.56,0:20:41.03,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,If you must hate someone, hate Tengen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:42.26,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(526.5,144)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HFAFAFA&}m 0 0 l 112 0 l 112 164 l 0 164
Dialogue: 1,0:20:39.00,0:20:42.26,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1225,0)\pos(526.5,144)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Q\NCombatant\N{\fs30}Kokun
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.51,0:20:42.26,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.87,0:20:47.13,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please stop making us stand out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:49.22,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,We just got chewed out \Nfor that this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:51.68,Italics,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,So this girl is the Star Plasma Vessel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.11,0:20:55.31,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,I know those uniforms. You're \Nsorcerers from Jujutsu High, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:20:56.77,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:20:58.36,Main,Kokun,0000,0000,0000,,Or I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.77,0:21:00.39,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Can't hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:02.40,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Come closer and talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.79,0:21:05.13,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Man, barely safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.56,0:21:11.16,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:14.16,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,You're Satoru Gojo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.16,0:21:16.12,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\pos(113.5,146)\p1\bord0\shad0\an5\c&HFAFAFA&}m 0 0 l 136 0 l 136 164 l 0 164
Dialogue: 1,0:21:14.16,0:21:16.12,Main,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\pos(113.5,146)\an5\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\fscy140\c&H000000&\bord0\shad0\b1}Q\NCombatant\N{\fs30}Bayer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.45,0:21:16.16,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,You're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.14,0:21:18.85,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you're strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.85,0:21:21.62,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,Let me find out if the rumors are true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.16,0:21:25.47,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm down for that, but let's set some rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.47,0:21:26.68,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,Rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.15,0:21:30.11,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to get yelled \Nat for going overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.38,0:21:33.52,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,So if you cry and apologize, \NI won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:34.98,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,That's our rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:36.58,Main,Bayer,0000,0000,0000,,Damn brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.32,0:21:40.04,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,It's started.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.99,0:21:44.70,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Religious Group doesn't have the \Npower to fight against jujutsu sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.01,0:21:46.61,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,But they can pay very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:48.39,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,That I guarantee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:50.75,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,How about it, Zen'in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.27,0:21:54.89,Main,Kong,0000,0000,0000,,Want to get in on the assassination \Nof the Star Plasma Vessel?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.60,0:21:57.68,Main,Toji,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a Zen'in anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.68,0:21:59.50,Main,Toji,0000,0000,0000,,I took my wife's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.84,0:22:01.47,Main,Toji,0000,0000,0000,,It's Fushiguro now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:03.49,Main,Toji,0000,0000,0000,,But sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.87,0:22:05.74,Main,Toji,0000,0000,0000,,Count me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.97,0:22:09.97,Ep_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 25\N{\fs30\fscy150}Hidden Inventory
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.60,0:23:42.19,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,You know how there are some \Nwords you can't get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.19,0:23:44.02,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,your head, even though they \Nhave no connection to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.02,0:23:45.64,Main,Geto,0000,0000,0000,,Like "The Privatization of \NReclaimed Lands in Perpetuity Act"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.64,0:23:47.50,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Or like "Corporate Governance."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:49.94,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please look forward to the next \Nepisode, "Hidden Inventory 2"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:54.99,Ep_Title,Screen,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\bord2\blur4}Next Episode\N{\fs30\fscy150}Hidden Inventory 2
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.94,0:23:50.99,Main,Gojo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You tell us one, too, Shoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:52.70,Main,Shoko,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Chagu Chagu Umakko.

